never leave the store.

09:57.830 --> 09:59.025
I'm not stealing this pen.

09:59.765 --> 10:02.506
I'm merely holding it,
openly in your presence

10:03.168 --> 10:05.313
Without any current
objections from you.

10:05.737 --> 10:08.996
The janitor will testify that he
was running for the exit. That's intent.

10:09.325 --> 10:11.966
Yeah, but aren't the cash
registers right by the exit?

10:12.377 --> 10:14.239
I think we'll take
our chances in court.

10:15.347 --> 10:18.550
Parker, what did the janitor
say to my client immediately

10:18.550 --> 10:19.646
after the accident?

10:20.686 --> 10:21.958
I'm looking.

10:23.322 --> 10:25.566
His first words
were, "I'm sorry."

10:26.859 --> 10:28.854
"I'm sorry, I forgot the sign."

10:29.236 --> 10:31.684
The big, yellow warning
sign that never left his cart.

10:32.331 --> 10:35.540
Now an employee of your
client apologized to my client

10:35.575 --> 10:37.028
moments after the incident.

10:37.169 --> 10:40.979
And he knew that he had duty
of care to place that sign out

10:41.747 --> 10:43.850
So customers would
know that that floor was wet.

10:45.244 --> 10:48.729
Now I suggest you drop those charges
before this becomes  an actual lawsuit.

10:52.518 --> 10:55.007
Like I said, we can
all just walk away.

10:57.589 --> 10:59.654
Oh... don't forget this.

11:04.296 --> 11:05.915
40... - Have a
good day, Parker.

11:08.934 --> 11:11.524
Before you go
and thank me, don't.

11:12.804 --> 11:14.148
I didn't do you any favors.

11:14.640 --> 11:16.730
I was assigned to you
because you didn't have a lawyer.

11:16.842 --> 11:19.240
I did what was my
legal responsibility.

11:19.411 --> 11:21.295
Everyone's entitled
to a vigorous defense.

11:21.413 --> 11:23.720
But let's get one
thing straight here, Polo...

11:24.216 --> 11:26.385
if you end up back in court
again, I am not gonna be here

11:26.385 --> 11:28.392
to save your
sorry tail. - Nope!

11:28.854 --> 11:30.615
Don't even think about suing.

11:30.622 --> 11:33.030
A second chance is worth
a lot more than money.

11:34.593 --> 11:35.647
Now go on, get.

12:21.873 --> 12:25.435
After ten years I would've at least
thought you'd have changed the locks.

12:26.545 --> 12:27.526
Pru.

12:28.436 --> 12:29.848
You know, you
always did have a knack

12:30.119 --> 12:31.271
for being one
step ahead of me.

12:38.023 --> 12:39.536
My brother's in trouble.

12:40.993 --> 12:42.734
He's always in trouble.
- Not like this.

12:44.496 --> 12:46.463
What's Jay gotten
himself into this time?

12:47.866 --> 12:48.990
It's murder.

12:50.736 --> 12:51.614
Murder?

12:52.771 --> 12:55.765
Who'd he go and kill?
- District attorney.

12:56.541 --> 12:58.076
A D.A., huh?

12:58.844 --> 13:00.644
Your brother's hit
the big time, babe.

13:01.404 --> 13:03.862
The arraignment's on monday.
- Back in Cherokee Hills?

13:09.588 --> 13:10.815
I didn't know
where else to go.

13:19.998 --> 13:21.671
How's your winning streak?

13:22.534 --> 13:23.495
39.

13:24.036 --> 13:25.862
Well, I'm glad our
divorce wasn't for nothing.

13:26.830 --> 13:28.583
Pru, now listen.
- Will you defend him or not?

13:31.743 --> 13:33.097
You're the best lawyer I know.

13:38.016 --> 13:39.480
You want me to
defend your brother,

13:40.886 --> 13:43.519
the same brother that
we've given a small fortune to?

13:45.057 --> 13:48.839
The brother who we bailed
out, dropped off, taken in

13:48.874 --> 13:51.863
and rescued more times
than a dog's had fleas? - Yeah.

13:53.336 --> 13:57.535
You remember the time he stayed over
and stole my grandmother's silver? - Yeah.

13:57.969 --> 13:59.597
Yeah, remember the
time he took mr. Darcy...

13:59.638 --> 14:01.943
Okay look, my list is longer
than yours, okay Casey? - Right.

14:02.908 --> 14:04.409
But, Jay's family.

14:05.344 --> 14:07.079
His whole life's
been on a downhill roll.

14:07.079 --> 14:09.157
Are you really surprised
that this is where he's landed?

14:11.350 --> 14:12.630
Still wearing your watch.

14:14.019 --> 14:17.096
I remember buying it for you.
- It stopped working a year ago.

14:18.423 --> 14:20.056
So why don't you
just get a new one?

14:22.728 --> 14:24.191
Some things are
worth hanging onto.

14:25.997 --> 14:28.559
Besides I'd rather get it fixed.

14:33.839 --> 14:34.909
Well...

14:35.607 --> 14:39.644
you may look different but...
you haven't changed a lick.

14:40.145 --> 14:42.432
Still too busy.
- Pru...

14:47.919 --> 14:50.502
What good's a winning streak
if you're not willing to risk it?

14:54.926 --> 14:56.311
Thank you, Casey.

16:08.467 --> 16:11.860
We've got a 10-91 at the court house.
Suspect, Jay Chambers, in custody.

16:27.752 --> 16:30.717
Books, bibles, magazines.

16:31.189 --> 16:33.215
Can I get you
anything before lights out?

16:35.827 --> 16:38.431
