21:43.935 --> 21:46.233
Don't you care that
justice is done at all?

21:46.471 --> 21:47.381
That's why I'm here.

21:47.447 --> 21:49.541
Everyone's innocent
till proven guilty.

21:49.541 --> 21:51.910
And as far as I'm
concerned, he's already standing.

21:51.910 --> 21:54.901
Well, mr. McKay call me
old fashioned but I think

21:55.697 --> 21:58.624
we ought to let
truth decide this case.

21:59.439 --> 22:02.076
Your brother-in-law just
graduated from Ne'er-do-well

22:02.253 --> 22:06.410
public enemy No1, so no sir, there
will be no plea deal, not for murder one.

22:07.196 --> 22:10.073
Not for Henry Patrick Jenkins
our late district attorney,

22:10.399 --> 22:13.215
and certainly not for
the likes of Jay Chambers,

22:13.331 --> 22:16.625
a man known to throw
bricks at cars from the overpass.

22:17.315 --> 22:18.473
Y'all have an overpass?

22:30.481 --> 22:32.708
Oh, hey I'm gonna need that.
I'm gonna have to take notes.

22:33.451 --> 22:35.874
I know he's a murder suspect, but
he's not gonna doodle me to death.

22:36.187 --> 22:37.744
Sorry, judge's orders.

22:43.428 --> 22:47.609
Jay. - Well, I see my sister still gets you
to do pretty much whatever she wants.

22:51.102 --> 22:52.728
So you here to
save the day?

22:55.406 --> 22:57.193
How about we
start saving your life?

22:57.234 --> 22:58.091
MURDERED D.A.'S
SUSPECT ARRAIGNED

23:04.282 --> 23:07.194
You always were the least
favorite of Pru's husbands.

23:07.585 --> 23:10.360
Well, considering she only had
one, I'll take that as a compliment.

23:14.713 --> 23:16.993
So what's the deal, Jay?
- I don't know.

23:17.495 --> 23:20.500
I mean, I killed somebody.
- Yeah, that's what I've heard.

23:21.021 --> 23:23.646
I also heard that somebody
crept into the courthouse

23:23.681 --> 23:25.192
wearing a mask
and killed the D.A..

23:25.570 --> 23:27.135
Henry Patrick Jenkins.

23:27.170 --> 23:29.693
That they've confirmed
your fingerprints on the gun,

23:29.728 --> 23:31.137
and your boot
prints on the floor.

23:31.643 --> 23:34.860
But, the thing that really made
the executioner smile extra wide

23:35.460 --> 23:37.771
is the fact that they nabbed
you fleeing the scene of the crime

23:38.050 --> 23:40.775
with all the aforementioned
on your person. - What?

23:42.117 --> 23:43.796
What... what do
you want from me?

23:44.188 --> 23:45.838
How about you
start by elaborating.

24:00.271 --> 24:01.589
Nah, I can't.

24:07.946 --> 24:09.380
Jay, what are you doing?

24:15.119 --> 24:17.443
I remember you used
to like puzzles, right?

24:19.157 --> 24:21.265
Read this paper. There's
a good one in there for ya.

24:48.653 --> 24:52.023
All rise! The honorable
judge Thorne presiding.

24:58.279 --> 25:01.200
The state of Georgia
versus Steven Jay Chambers.

25:01.666 --> 25:04.933
Counselor... your
client's been charged with...

25:05.303 --> 25:07.750
first degree murder.
How do you plead?

25:08.606 --> 25:10.588
Guilty.
- Not guilty, Your honor.

25:11.042 --> 25:12.961
Shh.
- What are you doing?

25:13.850 --> 25:16.126
You are not gonna have a leg
to stand on if you plead that.

25:16.415 --> 25:19.883
