take a recess while you and your client

25:19.918 --> 25:23.371
Discuss how he'd like to plead?
- No, Your honor. Not guilty.

25:24.555 --> 25:26.849
Your honor, I'd also like to
motion for a change of venue.

25:27.440 --> 25:29.449
On what grounds?
- Several, Your honor.

25:29.794 --> 25:30.951
Such as?

25:31.725 --> 25:33.446
Well, I'd rather not have
the jury sitting in the shadow

25:33.564 --> 25:34.934
of the crime scene,
Your honor.

25:35.995 --> 25:37.706
The crime scene is what it is,

25:37.741 --> 25:41.489
whether your client committed
the murder or not. Mr... uh.

25:42.440 --> 25:45.580
McKay, Your honor. - Mr. McKay,
there's been more blood shed

25:45.615 --> 25:50.413
within the shadow of that
jury box... than you'd care to know.

25:50.715 --> 25:55.211
This building... stood
between Sherman and the sea.

25:55.707 --> 26:00.578
There was the assassination of
judge Caliber in '63. The riots of '74.

26:00.872 --> 26:03.427
If I keel over
dead right now...

26:03.694 --> 26:07.579
I expect court to be in session
after lunch. - Yes, Your honor.

26:08.366 --> 26:09.777
I... I just...

26:11.239 --> 26:13.359
I'm not sure that my
client can get a fair trial

26:13.625 --> 26:17.997
of his peers in this community
based on his... past indiscretions.

26:18.076 --> 26:20.974
I feel that a local jury
would have a difficult time

26:21.145 --> 26:23.660
looking past their own
prejudice and preconceptions of

26:23.695 --> 26:25.660
who mr. Chambers was.

26:26.207 --> 26:29.575
Mr. McKay, this county
is made up of hard-working,

26:30.321 --> 26:33.224
God-fearing,
honorable men and women.

26:33.224 --> 26:37.035
I have no doubt that you'll be
able to find a fair and impartial jury.

26:37.604 --> 26:40.779
I understand that, but I'd prefer
an outside jury pool, Your honor.

